	   <tr><td colspan=2>I've had quill pop after an hour or 2 of tracking SK and killing escaped gnoll, brother dash, cyclops (dead or alive ones), any wondering birds/lions/wolfs/ect., and killing any random spawns i dont see more of one of on track such as a dwarven skeleton.&nbsp;&nbsp;Most times i do this quill does pop.  As for having a placeholder exactly that i kill, such as brother dash (which if you dont like the faction hits it should even out if you kill escaped gnoll), ive yet to find it and if you want quill i guess this is the best way i know how yet.   As for the times ive had quill pop, once was in the middle of the zone between birds and centi village, other was in the middle of the spires, and most others were around the spires in veiwing distance or at the walls.  As for giving the cloak to mages, some deserve if others dont.  Not to start a flame but on my server i get asked to track for quill because &quot;The mage has binded there and can gate in, they are in another zone thanks for ur time whatever they leave&quot; others sit on their butts doing god knows what.  if you want help from rangers, druids, or bards granted the ones you dont know as well, other go around the zone attemping to kill things that you see and bind at the spires since yes that is the most normal spawn point or pay people for their time not if you loot it.  I'd gladly help any mage who helped me kill things or one to paid me if they left not just for getting quill but for my time as well.  If that helps any i'm glad and if you offended by this post as well, then you're one of these lazy mages and should really understand it's an epic meaning you have to work on it as well even if you don't have track.<br><br>And also a side note, the old cloak is lore, someone who started in beta 2 and is still playing has one in the bank from a long time ago and yes it isn't now but at one point it was.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Thu Apr 11 07:40:59 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
