	   <tr><td colspan=2>I have a few suggestions with respect to this cloak. <br> <br>1) First of all, it doesn't say that it's LORE.&nbsp;&nbsp;Assuming that's true, the very next patch should change it to LORE.  That would prevent anyone from even considering killing Quill if they already had a cloak.<br><br>2) Increase the drop rate.  As a matter of fact, let it drop every time.  But the only way that would be practical, it to include my next change as well...<br><br>3) Make it Mage-only.  OK, stop screaming at me - keep reading.  As long as it's all/all, I absolutely agree that no one should be put into a position where they feel pressured into giving up the cloak, or guilty for looting it while some Mage is standing there imporing them to give it up.  Making it Mage-only will eliminate that problem.<br><br>4) Introduce some other all/all item that has the effect lev into the game.  It needs to be no more difficult to get that this cloak, and obtainable at the same level.<br><br>These changes, would reduce the tedium of only one of the stumbling blocks along the way to the Mage epic, while allowing those who want a lev item to still be able to get one.  The only people who would be negatively affected are those who want to camp the cloak to sell it as an MQ.<br><br>I want to point out that my goal is not to make the Mage epic easier, but to reduce tedium and make it more fair for everyone.<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Xtal Matrix<br>53rd Magician<br>Brell Serilis</td></tr>
