	   <tr><td colspan=2>Unfortunately, Verant is unlikely to change any epic-needed items to (insert-class-here)-item only. <br><br>Numerous items come to mind:<br><br>- Various robes needed for rogue epic: Talk about oddball pieces for a rogue to need (robes), so I have always wondered about the logic of that. :)&nbsp;&nbsp;And yet, 4 robes are needed for it! (Shiny Metallic Robe, Ishva Robes, Oracle Robes, and Robe of the Kedge)<br><br>- Enchanters also need the SMR, which, since it is AC10 INT9 svF8 svC8, is a very popular choice for the other classes that can wear it - NEC, WIZ, MAG<br><br>- Jade Reavers, needed by Rangers and Druids, and often one of the hardest pieces to get. (my chanter's guild on 7th had a chain-spawn of 9 Black Reavers and not one JR dropped ... d'oh!). War/SK/Pal can also weild this weapon, which is 23/40 2hs, so I've seen some peeps of these classes actually want to roll when these drop. <br><br>Those are just 3 that come to mind off the top of my head, I am sure there are plenty more. Unfortunately, there are a lot of people out there who farm these rare items for no other reason than to sell the items (whether direct trade or MQ) for ridiculous amounts of money to people of the classes desperate to get the pieces for their epics... the same people who can never get the camps because some farmer is sitting there. <br><br>Verant could solve a lot of problems for epics by making more epic-related items nodrop, but people would still sell rights to MQ quest items. (I'm always willing to help MQ on items I can't use, and do not charge ridiculous amts of pp to do so).<br><br>It would also be nice to see more of the dragon drops (ie Cloak of Flames) go to nodrop status. On my main server (7th) there is a rather well-known incident where a pally lead a raid on Naggy, and made the rolls all/all (except for epic book). So a cleric got in on the roll and won the CoF (which has up to 50% haste depending on your level) ... and the raid leader gave it to him... needless to say, neither of those guys (cleric or the pally leading raid) won any popularity contests that day. It'd be like allowing melee classes other than bard/warrior to roll on the dragon scale drop, just so they can go quest a BP that isn't even tops in the game.<br><br>Need before greed is a good thing, it's just too bad more players don't follow that ideal.<br><br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>Navarra Meritage<br>Ranger of 52 seasons<br>Stormhammer server</td></tr>
